# Object params

Convention (no backing skill — **no automated enforcement point; review-enforced**). Functions/methods with **2+ parameters** take a single named options object, **except** repository files and framework callbacks (Fastify `req`/`reply`, array callbacks). Reduces arg-order bugs, keeps call sites self-documenting and signatures stable. Detail: CLAUDE.md › Naming Conventions.
